parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: UConnect System Failure (Ghost Touching, Delamination, and Malfunction)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the UConnect system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses. The system's malfunction can also affect the vehicle's safety features, such as the backup camera and blind spot detectors.
symptoms: The UConnect screen delaminates
causing ghost touches and random activations of various functions
including the radio
climate control
and phone dialing. The system may also freeze or become unresponsive
and the backup camera may not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Faulty Wiring, Grounding, or Fuses)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety features to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The rear passenger tail light turns on and off randomly
the ABS and traction control lights come on and off while driving
and the brake pedal tightens up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination and malfunction of the UConnect screen can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents, and can also prevent the use of important safety features such as the backup camera.
symptoms: The screen is delaminating
the screen is melting
the screen is hot to the touch
random buttons are being selected
the screen is jumping from menu item to menu item
the backup camera is flickering
and the system is causing distractions while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Interior Door Panel Warping and Separation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warping and separation of the interior door panels can expose the electronic systems on the doors, including the locking mechanisms and window regulators, to moisture and heat, which can cause electrical failures and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The door panels are warping
the door panels are separating from the frame
the door panels are lifting and exposing the interior of the door plastics and electronics.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccuracy and freezing of the UConnect navigation system can cause drivers to become lost or disoriented, leading to accidents, and can also prevent the use of important safety features such as emergency services.
symptoms: The navigation system is showing incorrect locations
the system is freezing while driving or not turning off when the car is stopped
the system is affecting all UConnect features including phone
backup camera
and radio.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, leading to accidents, and can also prevent the use of important safety features such as the radio and heating and cooling systems.
symptoms: The vehicle is shutting off while driving
the radio is breaking up and shutting off
the heating and cooling systems are not working properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the interior door panel can cause issues with door controls, ventilation, and potentially even airbag deployment, which can lead to safety concerns and inconvenience.
symptoms: The interior door panel is warped
peeling
or lifting away from the door frame
exposing electrical wiring
foam
or other internal components; door controls
such as locks or windows
may malfunction; visual obstruction when looking over the shoulder.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous shattering of the sunroof can cause a safety hazard, potentially injuring occupants or other road users, and may lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters suddenly
sending glass flying down the back of the car
potentially causing cuts or other injuries.
